0year%20after%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFour%20more%20had%20their%20security%20clearances%20revoked.%20The%20inspector%20general%20found%20that%20although%20individuals%20engaged%20in%20misconduct%2C%20there%20was%20no%20evidence%20%26quot%3Bmisconduct%20is%20widespread%20in%20USSS.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJournalist%20Carol%20D.%20Leonnig%2C%20who%20won%20a%20Pultizer%20Prize%20for%20her%20coverage%20of%20the%20Secret%20Service's%20scandals%2C%20later%20called%20into%20question%20the%20finding%20that%20Colombia%20episode%20was%20just%20a%20one-off%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20in%20fact%2C%20what%20agents%20told%20me%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20this%20series%20of%20investigations%2C%20what%20they%20told%20me%20was%20this%20happened%20all%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Leonnig%20later%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2021%2F05%2F17%2F997377737%2Funderfunded-and-overworked-secret-service-fears-theyre-relying-on-luck%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThey%2520felt%2520that%2520he%2520was%2Cconvention%2520halls%2520for%252048%2520hours.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20NPR%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESecret%20Service%20Director%20Mark%20Sullivan%2C%20who%20retired%20not%20long%20after%20the%20scandal%2C%20testified%20to%20Congress%20that%20some%20of%20his%20agents%20%26quot%3Bdid%20some%20really%20dumb%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fc6b5c9d-7c13-484d-b2bf-bf3121e40779%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20knife-wielding%20intruder%20makes%20it%20all%20the%20way%20into%20the%20East%20Room.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happened%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20September%202014%2C%20Omar%20J.%20Gonzalez%2C%20who%20was%20carrying%20a%20knife%2C%20jumped%20the%20fence%20and%20got%20into%20the%20White%20House.%20President%20Barack%20Obama%20was%20not%20home%20at%20the%20time%20of%20the%20incident.%20Gonzalez%20only%20made%20it%20into%20the%20White%20House%20briefly%2C%20but%20his%20actions%20came%20on%20the%20heels%20of%2016%20separate%20fence-jumping%20incidents%20in%20the%20five%20years%20before%20his%20brazen%20act%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2014%2F09%2F30%2Fus%2Fwhite-house-intruder-got-farther-than-first-reported-official-says.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20aftermath%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESecret%20Service%20Director%20Julia%20Pierson%20was%20already%20embattled%20before%20the%20incident.%20In%20a%20separate%20scandal%2C%20an%20armed%20security%20contractor%20had%20gotten%20onto%20an%20elevator%20with%20Obama.%20The%20combined%20weight%20of%20the%20scandals%20led%20Pierson%20to%20resign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e1cba311-08dc-4b3d-be34-f6ce64707d5a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETwo%20Secret%20Service%20agents%2C%20who%20had%20'likely'%20been%20drinking%2C%20crashed%20a%20car%20on%20the%20White%20House%20grounds.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happened%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fobama-is-disappointed-by-the-latest-secret-service-scandal-2015-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20March%202015%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20two%20Secret%20Service%20agents%20crashed%20a%20car%20on%20the%20White%20House%20grounds%20while%20the%20complex%20was%20under%20a%20heightened%20security%20state%20to%20investigate%20a%20suspicious%20package.%20Both%20agents%20were%20high-ranking%2C%20including%20Marc%20Connolly%2C%20the%20Deputy%20Special%20Agent%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Presidential%20Protective%20Division%20(PPD.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20Connolly's%20responsibilities%20was%20handling%20%26quot%3Ball%20aspects%20of%20White%20House%20security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomeland%20Security%20Inspector%20General%20John%20Roth%2C%20a%20government%20watchdog%2C%20later%20concluded%20%26quot%3Bit%20was%20more%20likely%20than%20not%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20agents'%20%26quot%3Bjudgment%20was%20impaired%20by%20alcohol.%26quot%3B%20Roth's%20report%20found%20that%20the%20agents%20had%20attended%20a%20retirement%20party%20and%20run%20up%20quite%20the%20tab%20at%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20bar%20before%20the%20incident.%20Neither%20of%20the%20agents%20alerted%20their%20supervisors%20of%20what%20happened.%20Both%20of%20the%20agents%20denied%20in%20their%20interviews%20with%20the%20inspector%20general%20that%20they%20had%20drank%20to%20excess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20aftermath%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EConnolly%20announced%20his%20retirement%20ahead%20of%20the%20release%20of%20the%20inspector%20general's%20report.%20George%20Ogilvie%2C%20the%20assistant%20special%20agent%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20agency's%20Washington%20field%20office%2C%20was%20placed%20on%20administrative%20leave%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2015%2Fmay%2F14%2Fsecret-service-agent-retires-after-alcohol-finding-in-white-house-car-crash%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20The%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bfb36d46-f5f3-4ba3-bc42-d8387fd841c3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhite%20House%20fencer%20jumper%20wanders%20the%20grounds%20for%20more%20than%2015%20minutes.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happened%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20March%202017%2C%20Jonathan%20T.%20Tran%20scaled%20multiple%20fences%20and%20was%20able%20to%20approach%20the%20White%20House's%20south%20portico%20just%20before%20midnight.%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20was%20asleep%20inside%20the%20residence%20at%20the%20time.%20Tran%20also%20looked%20into%20windows.%20Secret%20Service%20later%20apprehended%20him.%20He%20had%20cans%20of%20mace%20on%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20aftermath%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAccording%20to%20CNN%2C%20two%20Secret%20Service%20officers%20were%20fired%20after%20the%20incident.%20Tran%20had%20set%20off%20multiple%20alarms%20before%20he%20was%20discovered.%20A%20White%20House%20security%20review%20was%20also%20conducted.%20Before%20the%20breach%2C%20the%20Secret%20Service%20had%20already%20announced%20efforts%20to%20beef%20up%20the%20fence%20around%20the%20White%20House%2C%20including%20adding%20small%20spikes%20atop%20a%20six-foot%20fence%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Washington%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22866ce67d-7358-46c9-951a-75532d2c7d68%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Secret%20Service%20caught%20wind%20of%20threats%20before%20January%206.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happened%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAccording%20to%20the%20House%20January%206%20committee%2C%20the%20Secret%20Service%20was%20among%20the%20federal%20agencies%20that%20received%20warnings%20that%20the%20far-right%20Proud%20Boys%20and%20Oath%20Keepers%20were%20planning%20for%20potential%20violence%20on%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20during%20the%20joint%20session%20of%20Congress%20that%20was%20responsible%20for%20formally%20counting%20the%20Electoral%20College%20votes%20for%20the%202020%20presidential%20election.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgents%20were%20also%20praised%20for%20how%20they%20kept%20Vice%20President%20Mike%20Pence%20safe%20as%20rioters%20ransacked%20the%20Capitol.%20Pence%20declined%20to%20leave%20the%20Capitol%20complex%2C%20which%20his%20security%20detail%20advised%20him%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20aftermath%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAfter%20the%20deadly%20attack%20on%20the%20Capitol%2C%20the%20Secret%20Service%20was%20also%20criticized%20after%20lawmakers%20asked%20for%20text%20messages%20sent%20around%20the%20time%20of%20the%20riot%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20agency%20said%20had%20been%20deleted.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Secret%20Service%20denied%20any%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-shooting-assassination-attempt-secret-service-past-scandals-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720984545000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22h