3Cp%3EThe%20AR-15-style%20rifle%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20guns%20in%20the%20US.%20It%20has%20also%20been%20a%20common%20denominator%20in%20some%20of%20the%20country's%20worst%20mass%20shootings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20key%20facts%20about%20the%20weapon%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Are%20AR-15s%20So%20Lethal%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AR-15%20is%20a%20semi-automatic%20weapon%2C%20meaning%20a%20user%20can%20fire%20multiple%20shots%20in%20quick%20succession.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20cousin%2C%20the%20M-16%2C%20has%20been%20used%20by%20the%20US%20military%20since%20Vietnam.%20While%20some%20military%20assault%20rifles%20are%20fully%20automatic%2C%20civilians%20are%20prohibited%20from%20owning%20such%20weapons%20in%20most%20circumstances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAR-15s%20fire%20high-velocity%20bullets%20that%20travel%20at%20triple%20the%20speed%20of%20a%20handgun%20round%2C%20are%20accurate%20over%20long%20distances%2C%20and%20cause%20expansive%2C%20devastating%20wounds%20to%20soft%20tissue%20and%20internal%20organs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20handguns%20account%20for%20more%20deaths%20per%20year%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20AR-15s%20have%20frequently%20been%20used%20in%20high-profile%20mass%20shootings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202022%2C%20a%20former%20student%20used%20an%20AR-15%20to%20shoot%20dead%20nineteen%20children%20and%20two%20teachers%20at%20Robb%20Elementary%20School%20in%20Uvalde%2C%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weapon%20was%20also%20used%20in%20October%202017%20in%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20where%20a%20gunman%20massacred%2060%20people%20at%20a%20music%20festival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECheap%20And%20Easy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBuying%20an%20AR-15%20is%20easy.%20Depending%20on%20the%20state%20of%20residence%2C%20a%20prospective%20owner%20can%20walk%20into%20a%20gun%20shop%20and%2C%20after%20presenting%20a%20valid%20ID%2C%20buy%20a%20rifle%20or%20shotgun%20provided%20they%20can%20pass%20a%20federal%20background%20check.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20process%20looks%20at%20a%20buyer's%20criminal%20history%20or%20whether%20they%20have%20ever%20been%20committed%20to%20a%20mental%20institution.%20But%20even%20this%20cursory%20check%20can%20be%20flouted%20in%20the%20case%20of%20private%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Rifle%20Association%20(NRA)%20touts%20the%20rifles%20for%20recreational%20target%20practice%20and%20home%20defense%2C%20but%20critics%20say%20their%20lethality%20means%20they%20do%20not%20belong%20in%20civilian%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20popularity%20of%20AR-15s%20in%20America%20is%20that%20they%20are%20widely%20customizable%2C%20with%20owners%20able%20to%20add%20scopes%2C%20large-capacity%20magazines%20and%20a%20plethora%20of%20other%20accessories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bureau%20of%20Alcohol%2C%20Tobacco%2C%20Firearms%20and%20Explosives%20does%20not%20know%20how%20many%20assault%20weapons%20there%20are%20in%20America%20--%20they%20are%20prohibited%20by%20federal%20law%20from%20keeping%20a%20gun%20registry%20database.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Washington%20Post%20poll%20in%202023%20estimated%20that%20one%20in%2020%20American%20adults%20own%20at%20least%20one%20AR-15.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBanned%20In%20Several%20States%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssault%20weapons%20were%20banned%20in%201994%20under%20president%20Bill%20Clinton%2C%20but%20the%20restriction%20lapsed%20in%202004%20amid%20pressure%20from%20the%20powerful%20NRA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFederal%20efforts%20at%20reforms%20to%20gun%20laws%20have%20been%20stymied%20ever%20since%2C%20with%20critics%20arguing%20that%20they%20infringe%20the%20constitutional%20right%20to%20own%20a%20firearm%2C%20enshrined%20in%20the%20Second%20Amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20states%2C%20like%20California%2C%20Illinois%2C%20Maryland%2C%20New%20Jersey%20and%20Washington%20DC%2C%20have%20however%20banned%20ownership%20of%20assault%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20claims%20its%20gun%20safety%20laws%20have%20helped%20save%2019%2C000%20lives%20in%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20administration%20moved%20to%20crack%20down%20on%20firearm%20sales%20at%20gun%20shows%20and%20online%20that%20evade%20federal%20background%20checks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20several%20Republican-led%20states%20quickly%20sued%20to%20block%20the%20measure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720973820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-05%2Fke9n696o_ar15style-rifles-_625x300_23_May_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthe-ar-15-one-of-americas-deadliest-most-popular-guns-used-in-trump-attack-6105457%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20attempted%20assassination%20of%20former%20US%20president%20Donald%20Trump%20with%20a%20semi-automatic%20rifle%20illustrates%20once%20again%20how%20easy%20it%20is%20for%20shooters%20in%20the%20US%20to%20get%20their%20hands%20on%20inexpensive%2C%20easy-to-use%2C%20military-style%20weapons.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthe-ar-15-one-of-americas-deadliest-most-popular-guns-used-in-trump-attack-6105457%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthe-ar-15-one-of-americas-deadliest-most-popular-guns-used-in-trump-attack-6105457%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthe-ar-15-one-of-americas-deadliest-most-popular-guns-used-in-trump-attack-6105457%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Told%20Officer%20About%20Shooter%20On%20Roof%20Minutes%20Before%20Attack%20On%20Trump%3A%20Witness%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETwo%20witnesses%20at%20Donald%20Trump's%20election%20rally%20in%20Pennsylvania%2C%20where%20he%20was%20attacked%2C%20claimed%20to%20have%20seen%20the%20shooter%2C%20with%20one%20recalling%20how%20the%20gunman%20moved%20from%20roof%20to%20roof%2C%20apparently%20scouting%20for%20a%20perfect%20perch%20to%20shoot%20at%20the%20former%20US%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI%20on%20Sunday%20identified%20the%20gunman%20as%20Thomas%20Matthew%20Crooks%2C%2020%2C%20from%20Bethel%20Park%2C%20Pennsylvania.%20Crooks%2C%20armed%20with%20an%20AR-style%20rifle%2C%20was%20killed%20by%20Secret%20Service%20personnel.%20He%20fired%20multiple%20shots%20at%20the%20stage%20from%20an%20%E2%80%9Celevated%20position%20outside%20of%20the%20rally%20venue%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20agency%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gunman%20was%20able%20to%20get%20close%20enough%20to%20shoot%20and%20injure%20Trump%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20huge%20failure%20of%20the%20security%20agencies%20tasked%20with%20providing%20cover%20for%20him%20ahead%20of%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20gunman%20was%20on%20a%20rooftop%20approximately%20%26quot%3B200%20to%20250%20yards%26quot%3B%20from%20where%20the%20former%20US%20president%20was%20addressing%20his%20supporters%2C%20US%20media%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20attendee%20named%20Ben%20Macer%2C%20he%20was%20up%20along%20the%20fence%20line%20and%20%26quot%3Bsaw%20the%20guy%20move%20from%20roof%20to%20roof%26quot%3B%2C%20CBS%20News%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMacer%20further%20said%20he%20told%20an%20officer%20that%20the%20shooter%20was%20on%20the%20roof%2C%20approximately%20%26quot%3B200%20to%20250%20yards%26quot%3B%20away%20from%20where%20Trump%20was%20addressing%20his%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20turned%20around%20to%20go%20back%20to%20where%20I%20was%2C%20it%20was%20when%20the%20gunshots%20started%2C%20and%20then%20it%20was%20just%20chaos%2C%20and%20we%20all%20came%20running%20away%2C%20and%20that%20was%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EButler%20resident%20Ryan%20Knight%2C%20another%20witness%20along%20the%20fence%20line%2C%20also%20said%20he%20saw%20the%20suspected%20shooter%20atop%20the%20American%20Glass%20Research%20building%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20walked%20over%20about%2020%20minutes%20before%20the%20shooting%20happened%20to%20stand%20along%20the%20fence%20line%20where%20Trump%20was.%20As%20I%20was%20doing%20that%2C%20I%20was%20right%20beside%20the%20AGR%20building%2C%20which%20had%20the%20shooter%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Knight%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20sitting%20there%2C%20a%20guy%20said%2C%20'Oh%20God%2C%20he%20had%20a%20gun.'%20When%20I%20looked%20up%2C%20there%20was%20a%20guy%20on%20top%20of%20the%20building%20with%20an%20M16%20with%20a%20blanket%2C%20pointing%20at%20the%20president.%20He%20starts%20shooting.%20Four%20to%20five%20shots%20rang%20out.%20I%20throw%20the%20guy%20I'm%20with%20to%20the%20ground.%20I%20jump%20to%20the%20ground%2C%20I%20look%20up%2C%20and%20I%20see%20his%20head%20get%20split%20up%20from%20the%20shot%20from%20the%20Secret%20Service%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Secret%20Service%20has%20confirmed%20that%20one%20attendee%20was%20killed%20and%20two%20others%20were%20critically%20injured%20in%20the%20shooting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20cops%20started%20flying%20over%2C%20pushing%20us%20out%2C%20they%20took%20my%20name%2C%20witness%20report%2C%20%5Band%5D%20cell%20phone%20number%20to%20go%20over%20what%20happened%20because%20there%20%5Bweren't%20many%5D%20eyewitnesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Knight%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20main%20thought%20is%20why%20wasn't%20the%20Secret%20Service%20on%20top%20of%20AGR%3F%20That's%20a%20very%20big%20vantage%20point%20to%20shoot%20at%20the%20president.%20How%20did%20that%20get%20missed%3F%26quot%3B%20Knight%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMacer%20said%20he%20did%20not%20get%2