n%20people%E2%80%99s%20minds%20and%20plates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecalling%20his%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F290130%2Forigin-of-samosa-sambhar-chaat-history-indian-food-recipes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efond%20memories%20of%20the%20snack%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20television%20journalist%2C%20food%20critic%2C%20and%20author%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Indian%20Pantry%E2%80%99%20(2018)%2C%20Vir%20Sanghvi%20writes%20in%20a%20blog%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20many%20memories%20of%20eating%20at%20the%20original%20Nizam%E2%80%99s.%20A%20large%20%3Cem%3Etawa%20%3C%2Fem%3E(pan)%20which%20I%20was%20assured%20was%20a%20hundred%20years%20old%20(the%20next%20time%20I%20went%2C%20they%20said%2060%20years%20old%2C%20so%20let%E2%80%99s%20just%20agree%20it%20was%20very%20old)%20was%20put%20on%20an%20open%20fire.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20cook%20had%20already%20rolled%20a%20%3Cem%3Emaida%20paratha%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Indian%20flatbread%20made%20of%20refined%20flour)%20on%20the%20%3Cem%3Etawa%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Then%2C%20he%20broke%20an%20egg%20on%20the%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20cooked%20it%20on%20both%20sides%20so%20that%20the%20result%20was%20part%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20part%20omelette.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20goes%20on%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%20never%20forget%20those%20days%20in%201986%20when%20I%20would%20eat%20a%20Nizam%E2%80%99s%20roll%20for%20lunch%20every%20day.%20I%20had%20just%20come%20from%20Bombay%2C%20had%20no%20experience%20of%20rolls%20(a%20Frankie%20does%20not%20count%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20afraid%2C%20despite%20the%20resemblances)%20and%20was%20blown%20away%20by%20the%20excellence%20of%20the%20Nizam%E2%80%99s%20version.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FScreenshot-2024-0